<sect3 id="sect_definingTextLongtextFields" label="1">
    <title id="title_definingTextLongtextFields">Defining text and longtext fields</title>
    <informaltable frame="none">
        <tgroup rowsep="0" cols="2" align="left" colsep="0">
            <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colwidth="3*"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry rowsep="1"/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Purpose</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>Table fields of the type <guimenuitem>TEXT</guimenuitem> are compared
                            to fields of the type <guimenuitem>LONGTEXT</guimenuitem> limited in
                            their length. However, it is possible to search for strings in text
                            fields but not in longtext fields. </para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Type specific field details</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>
                            <figure id="fig_textFieldDetails">
                                <title> Text field details</title>
                                <screenshot>
                                    <mediaobject>
                                        <imageobject>
                                            <imagedata fileref="./Screenshots/TextFieldDetails.jpg"
                                                format="JPEG" scalefit="1" width="237" depth="107"/>
                                        </imageobject>
                                    </mediaobject>
                                </screenshot>
                            </figure>
                        </para>
                        <para>Therefore, you have to define the following type specific details when
                            creating a text field:</para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>a <guilabel>Default value</guilabel> can be declared;</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>the <guilabel>Search mode</guilabel> has to be defined;</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>the <guilabel>Max length</guilabel> of the text has to be specified;</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>enabling the <guilabel>Fix length</guilabel> check box
                                    implicates that the text field will be set up as CHAR field in a
                                    relational data base instead as VARCHAR field and</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>activating the <guilabel>Case sensitive</guilabel> check box
                                    enables a case sensitive search.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Search mode</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>The search mode defines how character strings are searched in a text
                            field during a query. The search mode can be:</para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>unbound</guimenuitem>, i.e. it will be searched for
                                    entries containing the search string in the appropriate text
                                    field; </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>leftbound</guimenuitem>, i.e. it will be searched
                                    for entries beginning with the search string; </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>rightbound</guimenuitem>, i.e. it will be searched
                                    for entries ending with the search string. </para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry/>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
</sect3>
